.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "simple_shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX shell that reads and executes commands from standard input.
It supports both interactive and non-interactive modes.
.PP
In interactive mode, a prompt
.B "$ "
is displayed before each command. In non-interactive mode (piped input),
no prompt is shown.
.SH COMMANDS
The shell reads a line, splits it into tokens separated by spaces or tabs,
and executes the resulting command.
.PP
If the command name contains a slash, it is used as a direct path.
Otherwise, the shell searches for the executable in the directories listed
in the
.B PATH
environment variable. If the command is not found, the shell prints an
error to standard error and does
.I not
fork.
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment, one variable per line.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns the exit status of the last command executed, or
.B 127
if the command was not found.
.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ ./hsh
$ /bin/ls
$ ls -l /tmp
$ exit
.fi
.PP
Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ echo "ls -la" | ./hsh
$ echo "/bin/echo hello" | ./hsh
.fi
